What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Inverted Pouches Market?

Market Analysis and Insights :

Global Inverted Pouches Market

The inverted pouches market size is expected to grow at a compound annual growth rate of 9.50% for the forecast period of 2021 to 2028. Data Bridge Market Research report on inverted pouches market provides analysis and insights regarding the various factors expected to be prevalent throughout the forecasted period while providing their impacts on the market’s growth.

Inverted pouches are the type of flexible packaging solution, used to pack food items such as condiments, sauces and personal care products. Customers are increasingly tending towards items that proffer convenience and features such as portability, controlled dispensing, ease of opening, and resealability and are lightweight.

The inverted pouches market is expected to rise in demand due to the rise in consumer’s inclination towards products that offer portability. Also, the high demand from packaged products is also projected to impact the growth of the inverted pouches in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028. The rapid increase in the percentage of on-the-go consumers associated with high portability of the inverted pouch makes it a popular choice amongst the food packaging manufacturers, which is also anticipated to flourish the demand of the inverted pouches market owing to the above mentioned reasons and is also projected to grow substantially during the forecast period. Furthermore, the rise in necessity of high barrier packaging to make sure product safety and long shelf life are also expected to push the growth of inverted pouches market in the above mentioned forecast period. Inverted pouches have high barrier properties and also put in to low carbon emissions along with consumer convenience which is also anticipated to contribute to the growth of the market.

The major factor which actively drives the demand of inverted pouches market is the rapid increase in the R&D activities. Likewise, the inverted pouches find their maximum applicability across the food industry where the pouches are being used to keep food fresh for a longer period of time which is expected to offer various growth opportunities for the growth of inverted pouches market over the forecast period of 2021 to 2028.

However, the high cost of filling and sealing equipment are expected to impede the growth of the inverted pouches market in the above mentioned forecast period, whereas the unproductive dispensing of the traditional formats of packaging can challenge the growth of the inverted pouches market.

